<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 11:26AM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...HEAT INDEX VALUES OF 100 T0 105 EXPECTED THIS AFTERNOON INTO
THE EARLY EVENING...
Hot temperatures will combine with relatively high humidity levels
to produce heat index values of 100 to 105 between 100 PM and 700
PM today across the Piedmont and foothills of the Carolinas and
northeast Georgia. If spending time outdoors, try to limit
strenuous activities and wear loose-fitting, light-colored
clothing. If working outdoors is necessary, stay hydrated, and
take breaks in the shade as often as possible.
Young children and pets should never be left unattended in
vehicles under any circumstances. This is especially true during
warm or hot weather when car interiors can reach lethal
temperatures in a matter of minutes.</description>
